      • executeWithoutAccessCheck

        public void executeWithoutAccessCheck(OutputStream _out)
                               throws EFapsException
        Executes the checkout for output streams without checking the access rights (but with triggers).
        1. executes the pre checkout trigger (if exists)
        2. executes the checkout trigger (if exists)
        3. executes if no checkout trigger exists or the checkout trigger is not executed the update (executeWithoutTrigger(java.io.OutputStream))
        4. executes the post checkout trigger (if exists)
        Parameters:
        _out - output stream where to write the file
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if checkout action fails

      • execute

        public InputStream execute()
                    throws EFapsException
        Executes the checkout and returns an input stream by calling method executeWithoutAccessCheck().
        Returns:
        input stream of the checked in file
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if the current context user has now access to checkout the file out of the eFaps object
        See Also:
        executeWithoutAccessCheck()

      • executeWithoutAccessCheck

        public InputStream executeWithoutAccessCheck()
                                      throws EFapsException
        Executes the checkout without an access check (but with triggers) and returns an input streams of the checked in file. The returned input stream must be closed, because the returned inputs stream also commit the store resource. Otherwise the transaction is rolled back!
        1. executes the pre checkout trigger (if exists)
        2. executes the checkout trigger (if exists)
        3. executes if no checkout trigger exists or the checkout trigger is not executed the update (executeWithoutTrigger(java.io.OutputStream))
        4. executes the post checkout trigger (if exists)
        Returns:
        input stream containing the file
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if checkout action fails

      • executeWithoutTrigger

        public InputStream executeWithoutTrigger()
                                  throws EFapsException
        Executes the checkout without an access check and without triggers and returns an input streams of the checked in file. The returned input stream must be closed, because the returned inputs stream also commit the store resource. Otherwise the transaction is rolled back!
        Returns:
        input stream containing the file
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if checkout action fails
